                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.71114A/9–2544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-30T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 30, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2327. Department has been informed by American Legation Bern<note n="68"
                        xml:id="d745fn68">Telegram 6359, September 25, 6 p.m., not printed.</note>
                    that according to information received informally and orally the only
                    communication with Rumania is by telegraph in plain language. Legation states
                    that Swiss Foreign Office telegraphed to ascertain whether its representative
                    could continue protecting American interests until American representatives
                    could arrive and Minister’s reply was an inquiry as to when they would reach
                    there and that it is believed by Foreign Office that Swiss representative will
                    be unable to represent our interests and it strongly advises that an American
                    representative arrive at Bucharest very soon. The matter of American
                    representation in Rumania is being covered in a separate telegram.<note n="69"
                        xml:id="d745fn69">Telegram 2365, October 5, 8 p.m., <ref
                            target="frus1944v04#pg_246">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            246</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
